   <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;I’m excited to announce that I’ll be presenting &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://ndcoslo.com/talk/scaling-large-angular-apps/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Scaling Large Angular Apps&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://ndcoslo.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;NDC Oslo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; - Norway.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;NDC Oslo is one of the biggest developer conferences in Europe. With more than 150 speakers this year, covering over 40 technologies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here’s the abstract of my talk:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Scaling beyond the To Do list App of Angular JS. Although Angular JS is a powerful framework, we still need conventions, automation and a variety of tools to make it scale. Especially in a team environment. Learn how to scale your angular apps with simple but effective techniques, endorsed by the Angular community.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;This talk will include concepts applicable to both newest angular versions (2 and 1.5)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Are you going to NDC Oslo? If yes, let me know in the comments!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

